Soldiers punish lockdown violators in River State Security operatives in Port Harcourt have forced some lockdown violators who were among those rounded up in Port Harcourt and Obio/Akpor Local Government areas of Rivers State yesterday May 7, to sing ‘Coronavirus song’ after their arrest. This is coming after Governor Nyesom Wike had imposed a total lockdown in the local governments, following increased cases of Coronavirus in the area. Some young men who were arrested yesterday, were heard singing “Corona bye bye o” after being forced to sit at a spot. It is however unclear if they were taken to an isolation center in the state for Quarantine. Here is the video below; Lockdown violators sing the “Corona” song after arrest in Rivers state A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on May 8, 2020 at 3:25am PDT Source Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, has impounded two trailers loaded with cows and heading for Port Harcourt, the state capital, despite the 24-hour lockdown to check the Coronavirus pandemic in the capital city. The governor according to a statement signed by his Special Assistant on Electronic Media, Simeon Nwakaudu, also… May 8, 2020 In "News" In a bid to stop the importation of the novel Coronavirus to the state, Rivers state governor, Nyesom Wike, has declared that any oil worker who intends to come into the state for work, must present his or her COVID-19 test result before they will be allowed access into the… May 5, 2020 In "Politics" The Police Command in Kano on Tuesday confirmed it had arrested 30 youths allegedly involved in a football match in defiance to the lockdown order imposed on the state to contain the spread of the Coronavirus virus. Mr Abdullahi Haruna, the Commands’ spokesman, made the disclosure in an interview with… April 22, 2020 In "News"